description:
@BsonProperty is not being applied in ADT case classes:
{code:scala}
sealed class Tree
case class Branch(@BsonProperty("someName") b1: Tree, b2: Tree, value: Int) extends Tree
case class Leaf(value: Int) extends Tree
collection.insertOne(Branch(Branch(Leaf(1),Leaf(2), 3),Leaf(4),5))
{code}

gets saved as 
{code:json}{
  "_id" : ObjectId("5c207fd77aa018cccb795f38"),
  "_t" : "Branch",
  "b1" : {
    "_t" : "Branch",
    "b1" : {
      "_t" : "Leaf",
      "value" : 1
    },
  "b2" : {
    "_t" : "Leaf",
    "value" : 2
    },
  "value" : 3
  },
  "b2" : {
    "_t" : "Leaf",
    "value" : 4
  },
  "value" : 5
}
{code}

It seems that `IterableObservable` causes stack overflow, when used with `uploadFromObservable`.

Take a look at the following code:
{code:java}
def saveFileContent(fileId: FileId, content: InputStream): Future[Unit] = {
  //based on https://gist.github.com/alexandru/88aa2fe6a3fb453126a66b23ba200d96
  def fromInputStream(in: java.io.InputStream, chunkSize: Int = 256): Observable[ByteBuffer] = {
    val iterator: Iterator[ByteBuffer] = new Iterator[ByteBuffer] {
      private[this] val buffer = new Array[Byte](chunkSize)
      private[this] var lastCount = 0

      def hasNext: Boolean =
        lastCount match {
          case 0 =>
            lastCount = in.read(buffer)
            lastCount >= 0
          case nr =>
            nr >= 0
        }

      def next(): ByteBuffer = {
        if (lastCount < 0)
          throw new NoSuchElementException()
        else {
          val result = java.util.Arrays.copyOf(buffer, lastCount)
          lastCount = 0
          ByteBuffer.wrap(result)
        }
      }
    }

    Observable(iterator.toStream)
  }

  gridFSBucket.uploadFromObservable(
    toBsonValue[String](fileId.id), fileId.id,
    fromInputStream(content)
  ).toFuture().toUnit
}
{code}
It works fine as long as the chunkSize is big and it uploads the whole file in a low number of iterations. When te chunkSize is small, it causes stack overflow:
